The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro Briefs

 Work 

 on the Vivekananda Road flyover and the two-tier flyover connecting 

 Park Circus and Parama island will not begin until the projects 

 are thoroughly discussed with all the stakeholders. After 

 the CMDA board meeting on Thursday, urban development minister 

 Asok Bhattacharya said consultants CES suggested in a project 

 report that a section of the Brabourne Road flyover be demolished 

 to construct the Vivekananda Road flyover. 

 Urban 

 development minister Asok Bhattacharya was stuck inside a 

 VIP elevator in Writers Buildings on Thursday evening for 

 around three minutes. Policemen forced open the lift door. 

 Kumari 

 Devi, 55, was killed after being struck by lightning in the 

 balcony of her DL Khan Road home on Wednesday night. Her son 

 Chandan Das suffered serious injuries. 

 An 

 unidentified middle-aged man committed suicide by jumping 

 in front of a Dum Dum-bound Metro train at MG Road station 

 around 8.30 pm on Thursday. Services were disrupted for around 

 25 minutes. 

 Amina 

 Begum, 25, was allegedly burnt alive by her husband and in-laws 

 at Baruipur on Thursday morning. Police said the womans parents 

 complained that Amina used to be tortured for dowry. 




